{"title_page": "G. Barrett Rich", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Underlinked|date=April 2020}}\n{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n}}\n\n'''G. Barrett Rich''' (August 11, 1875<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://richfamilyassociation.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/RichFamilyNYBurialsByFirstName.pdf|title=Rich Family NY Burials|last=|first=|date=|website=Rich Family Association|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> - August 18, 1961)<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1961/08/20/archives/g-barrett-rich.html|title=G. Barrett Rich|date=1961-08-20|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-16|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> was the inspiration behind the G Barrett Rich Mansion<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://buffaloah.com/a/main/1313/landmk.html#barrett|title=Application for Landmark Site Status Saint Vincent's Female Orphan Asylum|website=buffaloah.com|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> and winner of the [[Silver Buffalo Award]] \u2013 the highest commendation from the [[Boy Scouts of America]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://scoutingmagazine.org/silverbuffalo/|title=Scouting magazine: List of Silver Buffalo recipients|website=Scouting magazine|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> He was a businessman<ref>{{Cite book|last=Macleod|first=David I.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=fo2pyMMOejIC&pg=PA350&lpg=PA350&dq=G.+Barrett+Rich,+BSA,+bio&source=bl&ots=sspmplpw2D&sig=ACfU3U2bIhDpdDLE0z7BzTdLYDMnBWD1IQ&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwit5Oe13sXkAhUD2KQKHVEEDKQQ6AEwAHoECAkQAQ#v=onepage&q=G.%20Barrett%20Rich,%20BSA,%20bio&f=false|title=Building Character in the American Boy: The Boy Scouts, YMCA, and Their Forerunners, 1870-1920|date=September 2004|publisher=Univ of Wisconsin Press|isbn=978-0-299-09404-1|language=en}}</ref> who held numerous executive roles including: president of the Bank of Attica (later known as The Buffalo Commercial Bank),<ref>{{Cite book|last=Poor|first=Henry Varnum|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=b220U4jsviQC&pg=PA625&lpg=PA625&dq=G+Barrett+Rich,+The+Buffalo+Commercial+Bank&source=bl&ots=HZoszCUC5e&sig=ACfU3U1LDFI1e9kYJbKU-qvVHM9oEK6uAg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjJ6dOt6cXkAhUH16QKHf9-CbIQ6AEwAXoECAkQAQ#v=onepage&q=G%20Barrett%20Rich,%20The%20Buffalo%20Commercial%20Bank&f=false|title=Poor's Hand Book of Investment Securities; for the Use of Bankers, Investors, Trust Institutions and Railroad Officials: Supplementing Poor's Manual of Railroads|date=1892|publisher=H.V. & H.W. Poor|language=en}}</ref> an incorporator and director of the Commonwealth Trust Company<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=fn1LAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA912&lpg=PA912&dq=G+Barrett+Rich,+Commonwealth+Trust+Company&source=bl&ots=Vgtt1hXmJK&sig=ACfU3U0unTuuxhWqXL2sOrtQv8o9LoLjRA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiHrMnG7sXkAhUiMuwKHdEXCoQQ6AEwAXoECAkQAQ#v=onepage&q=G%20Barrett%20Rich,%20Commonwealth%20Trust%20Company&f=false|title=Rand McNally International Bankers Directory|date=July 1905|publisher=Rand McNally & Company|language=en}}</ref> a trustee of the Erie County Savings Bank;<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/77485652/gaius-barrett-rich|title=Gaius Barrett Rich (1849-1923) - Find A Grave...|website=www.findagrave.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> Buffalo Public Library executive committee member<ref>{{Cite book|last=Inc|first=Boy Scouts of America|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vpaiL2cDZYYC&pg=PA26&lpg=PA26&dq=G+Barrett+Rich,+BSA&source=bl&ots=ZEA6smPk2K&sig=ACfU3U2r2CybJfqujvNoj4P8BkVTOjuGIg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjG0-Th4sXkAhVnUhUIHSR2AcUQ6AEwC3oECAcQAQ#v=onepage&q=G%20Barrett%20Rich,%20BSA&f=false|title=Boys' Life|date=August 1926|publisher=Boy Scouts of America, Inc.|language=en}}</ref> YMCA life member<ref>{{Cite book|last=Macleod|first=David I.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=fo2pyMMOejIC&pg=PA401&lpg=PA401&dq=G+Barrett+Rich,+YMCA&source=bl&ots=sspmplur2z&sig=ACfU3U397NA1IOgX9n7lB69fsqL0BG_e8A&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjpmvKV78XkAhVB2KQKHTXWDecQ6AEwDXoECAkQAQ#v=onepage&q=G%2