{"title_page": "Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\"", "text_new": "{{Infobox military award\n|name= Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\"\n|image=Guard of USSR Borders.jpg\n|image_size=200px\n|caption= Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\" (obverse)\n|awarded_by={{flag|USSR}} \n|type= Military medal\n|eligibility=Soviet border troops, servicemen and civilians\n|for=Outstanding military deeds related to state frontier security\n|campaign=\n|status=No longer awarded\n|description=\n|clasps=\n|established=July 13, 1950\n|first_award=\n|last_award=\n|total=67,000\n|posthumous=\n|recipients=\n|individual=\n|higher=\n|same=\n|lower=\n|related=\n|image2=[[File:GuardRibbon.png|80px]]\n|caption2=Ribbon of the Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\"\n}}\n[[File:Soviet border guard medal reverse.jpg|150px|thumb|right|Reverse of the Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\"]]\nThe '''Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\"''' ({{lang-ru|\u041c\u0435\u0434\u0430\u043b\u044c \u00ab\u0417\u0430 \u043e\u0442\u043b\u0438\u0447\u0438\u0435 \u0432 \u043e\u0445\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0435 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0446\u044b \u0421\u0421\u0421\u0420\u00bb}}) was a military decoration of the [[Soviet Union]] established to recognise outstanding deeds related to state frontier security by members of [[Soviet Border Troops]], servicemen and civilians.\n\n==Medal history==\nThe Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\" was established on July 13, 1950 by Decree of the [[Presidium of the Supreme Soviet of the USSR]].<ref name=\"border\">{{cite web  | authorlink = Russian Government | title = Decree of the Presidium of the Supreme Soviet of the USSR of July 13, 1950 | publisher = Legal Library of the USSR | date= 1950-07-13 | url = http://www.libussr.ru/doc_ussr/ussr_4786.htm | language = Russian | accessdate =2012-04-07}}</ref>  Its statute was amended on two occasions by further decrees of the Presidium of the Supreme Soviet of the USSR, firstly on March 18, 1977<ref name=\"border2\">{{cite web  | authorlink = Russian Government | title = Decree of the Presidium of the Supreme Soviet of the USSR of March 18, 1977 | publisher = Legal Library of the USSR | date= 1977-03-18 | url = http://www.libussr.ru/doc_ussr/ussr_4786.htm | language = Russian | accessdate =2012-04-07}}</ref>  and lastly on July 18, 1980.<ref name=\"Multi amendments\">{{cite web  | authorlink = Russian Government | title = Decree of the Presidium of the Supreme Soviet of the USSR of  July 18, 1980 \u2116 2523-X  | publisher = Legal Library of the USSR | date= 1980-07-18 | url = http://www.libussr.ru/doc_ussr/usr_10402.htm | language = Russian | accessdate =2012-04-07}}</ref>\n\n==Medal statute==\nThe Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\" was awarded to soldiers of Border Troops and other military personnel as well as to Soviet citizens for military exploits and special services displayed in the protection of the state borders of the USSR.<ref name=\"border\"/>  More precisely:\n*for bravery and selflessness displayed during combat operations aimed at the arrest of violators of the State Border of the USSR;\n*for the leadership of border protection units while ensuring the inviolability of the borders of the USSR;\n*for a high degree of vigilance and proactive actions which resulted in the arrest of violators of the State Border of the USSR;\n*for the skilful organization of border service units and exemplary work to strengthen the borders of the USSR;\n*for the excellent performance of military duties associated with the protection of the state borders of the USSR;\n*for active assistance to border protection forces in their combat assignments aimed at the protection of the state borders of the USSR.<ref name=\"border2\"/>\n\nThe Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\" was bestowed on behalf of the Presidium of the Supreme Soviet of the USSR by the Chairman of the [[KGB|Committee for State Security]].<ref name=\"border\"/>  It was worn on the left side of the chest and in the presence of other medals of the Soviet Union, immediately following the Medal \"Partisan of the Patriotic War\" 2nd class.<ref name=\"border2\"/>  When worn in the presence of orders and medals of the Russian Federation, the latter have precedence.<ref name=\"decree1099\">{{cite web  | authorlink = Russian Government | title = Decree of the President of the Russian Federation of September 7, 2010 No 1099 | publisher = Russian Gazette | date = 2010-09-07 | url = http://www.rg.ru/2010/09/15/nagrady-dok.html | language = Russian | accessdate =2012-04-07}}</ref>\n     \nThe Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\" awarded to those killed on duty or that have died, along with their relevant award certificates, are transferred to the families for safekeeping and as a memento.<ref name=\"Multi amendments\"/>\n\n==Medal description==\nThe Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\" was a 32\u00a0mm in diameter circular medal with a raised rim on both sides.  The medal was initially struck from silver, after 1966 it was constructed of silver-plated nickel and later of cupro-nickel.  The obverse bore the relief image of an erect border guard holding a [[PPSh-41]] submachine gun standing guard beside a border marker with high mountains in the background.  The reverse bore a relief inscription on six lines \"For Distinction in the Protection of the State Border of the USSR\" ({{lang-ru|\u00ab\u0417\u0430 \u043e\u0442\u043b\u0438\u0447\u0438\u0435 \u0432 \u043e\u0445\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0435 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0446\u044b \u0421\u0421\u0421\u0420\u00bb}}), at the top, the relief image of a five pointed star, at the bottom, a relief hammer and sickle over laurel and oak branches.<ref name=\"border\"/>\n\nThe Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\" was secured by a ring through the medal suspension loop to a standard Soviet pentagonal mount covered by a 24\u00a0mm wide green silk [[moir\u00e9]] ribbon with 3mm wide red edge stripes.<ref name=\"border\"/>\n\n==Recipients (partial list)==\nThe individuals below were all recipients of the Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\".\n\n*[[Viktor Trufanov|Coast Guard Colonel General Viktor Trofimovich Trufanov]]\n*[[Erich Mielke|East German Minister of State Security Erich Fritz Emil Mielke]]\n*[[Dmitriy Ustinov|Marshal of the Soviet Union and Defence Minister Dmitriy Feodorovich Ustinov]]\n*[[Yury Glazkov|Major General cosmonaut Yury Nikolayevich Glazkov]]\n*[[Sergey Akhromeyev|Marshal of the Soviet Union Sergey Fyodorovich Akhromeyev]]\n*[[Sergei Sokolov (Marshal)|Marshal of the Soviet Union Sergei Leonidovich Sokolov]]\n*[[Semyon Kurkotkin|Marshal of the Soviet Union Semyon Konstantinovich Kurkotkin]]\n*[[Vasily Ivanovich Petrov|Marshal of the Soviet Union Vasily Ivanovich Petrov]]\n*[[Alexey Maresyev|Colonel Alexey Petrovich Maresyev]]\n*[[Ivan Fedyuninsky|Army General Ivan Ivanovich Fedyuninsky]]\n*[[Sagadat Nurmagambetov|Army General Sagadat Kozhahmetovich Nurmagambetov]]\n*[[Boris Volynov|Cosmonaut Colonel Boris Valentinovich Volynov]]\n*[[Yury Artyukhin|Cosmonaut Colonel Yury Petrovich Artyukhin]]\n*[[Gennadi Sarafanov|Cosmonaut Colonel Gennadi Vasiliyevich Sarafanov]]\n*[[Vitaly Zholobov|Cosmonaut Colonel Vitaly Mikhaylovich Zholobov]]\n*[[Ilya Starinov|Colonel Ilya Grigoryevich Starinov]]\n\n==See also==\n*[[Soviet Border Troops]]\n*[[Medal \"For Distinction in the Protection of the State Borders\"|Russian Federation Medal \"For Distinction in the Protection of the State Borders\"]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.libussr.ru Legal Library of the USSR]\n*[http://www.rg.ru The Russian Gazette]\n{{Soviet awards}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Medal For Distinction In Guarding The State Border Of The Ussr}}\n[[Category:Military awards and decorations of the Soviet Union]]\n[[Category:Awards established in 1950]]\n[[Category:1950 establishments in the Soviet Union]]\n[[Category:Soviet Border Troops]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox military award\n|name= Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\"\n|image=Guard of USSR Borders.jpg\n|image_size=200px\n|caption= Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\" (obverse)\n|awarded_by={{flag|USSR}} \n|type= Military medal\n|eligibility=Soviet border troops, servicemen and civilians\n|for=Outstanding military deeds related to state frontier security\n|campaign=\n|status=No longer awarded\n|description=\n|clasps=\n|established=July 13, 1950\n|first_award=\n|last_award=\n|total=67,000\n|posthumous=\n|recipients=\n|individual=\n|higher=\n|same=\n|lower=\n|related=\n|image2=[[File:GuardRibbon.png|80px]]\n|caption2=Ribbon of the Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\"\n}}\n[[File:Soviet border guard medal reverse.jpg|150px|thumb|right|Reverse of the Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\"]]\nThe '''Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\"''' ({{lang-ru|\u041c\u0435\u0434\u0430\u043b\u044c \u00ab\u0417\u0430 \u043e\u0442\u043b\u0438\u0447\u0438\u0435 \u0432 \u043e\u0445\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0435 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0446\u044b \u0421\u0421\u0421\u0420\u00bb}}) was a military decoration of the [[Soviet Union]] established to recognise outstanding deeds related to state frontier security by members of [[Soviet Border Troops]], servicemen and civilians.\n\n==Medal history==\nThe Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\" was established on July 13, 1950 by Decree of the [[Presidium of the Supreme Soviet of the USSR]].<ref name=\"border\">{{cite web  | authorlink = Russian Government | title = Decree of the Presidium of the Supreme Soviet of the USSR of July 13, 1950 | publisher = Legal Library of the USSR | date= 1950-07-13 | url = http://www.libussr.ru/doc_ussr/ussr_4786.htm | language = Russian | accessdate =2012-04-07}}</ref>  Its statute was amended on two occasions by further decrees of the Presidium of the Supreme Soviet of the USSR, firstly on March 18, 1977<ref name=\"border2\">{{cite web  | authorlink = Russian Government | title = Decree of the Presidium of the Supreme Soviet of the USSR of March 18, 1977 | publisher = Legal Library of the USSR | date= 1977-03-18 | url = http://www.libussr.ru/doc_ussr/ussr_4786.htm | language = Russian | accessdate =2012-04-07}}</ref>  and lastly on July 18, 1980.<ref name=\"Multi amendments\">{{cite web  | authorlink = Russian Government | title = Decree of the Presidium of the Supreme Soviet of the USSR of  July 18, 1980 \u2116 2523-X  | publisher = Legal Library of the USSR | date= 1980-07-18 | url = http://www.libussr.ru/doc_ussr/usr_10402.htm | language = Russian | accessdate =2012-04-07}}</ref>\n\n==Medal statute==\nThe Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\" was awarded to soldiers of Border Troops and other military personnel as well as to Soviet citizens for military exploits and special services displayed in the protection of the state borders of the USSR.<ref name=\"border\"/>  More precisely:\n*for bravery and selflessness displayed during combat operations aimed at the arrest of violators of the State Border of the USSR;\n*for the leadership of border protection units while ensuring the inviolability of the borders of the USSR;\n*for a high degree of vigilance and proactive actions which resulted in the arrest of violators of the State Border of the USSR;\n*for the skilful organization of border service units and exemplary work to strengthen the borders of the USSR;\n*for the excellent performance of military duties associated with the protection of the state borders of the USSR;\n*for active assistance to border protection forces in their combat assignments aimed at the protection of the state borders of the USSR.<ref name=\"border2\"/>\n\nThe Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\" was bestowed on behalf of the Presidium of the Supreme Soviet of the USSR by the Chairman of the [[KGB|Committee for State Security]].<ref name=\"border\"/>  It was worn on the left side of the chest and in the presence of other medals of the Soviet Union, immediately following the Medal \"Partisan of the Patriotic War\" 2nd class.<ref name=\"border2\"/>  When worn in the presence of orders and medals of the Russian Federation, the latter have precedence.<ref name=\"decree1099\">{{cite web  | authorlink = Russian Government | title = Decree of the President of the Russian Federation of September 7, 2010 No 1099 | publisher = Russian Gazette | date = 2010-09-07 | url = http://www.rg.ru/2010/09/15/nagrady-dok.html | language = Russian | accessdate =2012-04-07}}</ref>\n     \nThe Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\" awarded to those killed on duty or that have died, along with their relevant award certificates, are transferred to the families for safekeeping and as a memento.<ref name=\"Multi amendments\"/>\n\n==Medal description==\nThe Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\" was a 32mm in diameter circular medal with a raised rim on both sides.  The medal was initially struck from silver, after 1966 it was constructed of silver-plated nickel and later of cupro-nickel.  The obverse bore the relief image of an erect border guard holding a [[PPSh-41]] submachine gun standing guard beside a border marker with high mountains in the background.  The reverse bore a relief inscription on six lines \"For Distinction in the Protection of the State Border of the USSR\" ({{lang-ru|\u00ab\u0417\u0430 \u043e\u0442\u043b\u0438\u0447\u0438\u0435 \u0432 \u043e\u0445\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0435 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0446\u044b \u0421\u0421\u0421\u0420\u00bb}}), at the top, the relief image of a five pointed star, at the bottom, a relief hammer and sickle over laurel and oak branches.<ref name=\"border\"/>\n\nThe Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\" was secured by a ring through the medal suspension loop to a standard Soviet pentagonal mount covered by a 24mm wide green silk [[moir\u00e9]] ribbon with 3mm wide red edge stripes.<ref name=\"border\"/>\n\n==Recipients (partial list)==\nThe individuals below were all recipients of the Medal \"For Distinction in Guarding the State Border of the USSR\".\n\n*[[Viktor Trufanov|Coast Guard Colonel General Viktor Trofimovich Trufanov]]\n*[[Erich Mielke|East German Minister of State Security Erich Fritz Emil Mielke]]\n*[[Dmitriy Ustinov|Marshal of the Soviet Union and Defence Minister Dmitriy Feodorovich Ustinov]]\n*[[Yury Glazkov|Major General cosmonaut Yury Nikolayevich Glazkov]]\n*[[Sergey Akhromeyev|Marshal of the Soviet Union Sergey Fyodorovich Akhromeyev]]\n*[[Sergei Sokolov (Marshal)|Marshal of the Soviet Union Sergei Leonidovich Sokolov]]\n*[[Semyon Kurkotkin|Marshal of the Soviet Union Semyon Konstantinovich Kurkotkin]]\n*[[Vasily Ivanovich Petrov|Marshal of the Soviet Union Vasily Ivanovich Petrov]]\n*[[Alexey Maresyev|Colonel Alexey Petrovich Maresyev]]\n*[[Ivan Fedyuninsky|Army General Ivan Ivanovich Fedyuninsky]]\n*[[Sagadat Nurmagambetov|Army General Sagadat Kozhahmetovich Nurmagambetov]]\n*[[Boris Volynov|Cosmonaut Colonel Boris Valentinovich Volynov]]\n*[[Yury Artyukhin|Cosmonaut Colonel Yury Petrovich Artyukhin